
    ePDFView Installation Instructions (GTK4)
    ==========================================

    NOTE: This is the GTK4 version of ePDFView. The build system has been
    migrated from Autotools to Meson/Ninja.

    PREREQUISITES
    =============

    Required packages:
    - GTK4 (>= 4.0.0)
    - Poppler with GLib bindings (>= 0.5.0)
    - GLib2 (>= 2.0)
    - Pango
    - Meson build system (>= 0.50)
    - Ninja build tool
    - pkg-config

    Optional:
    - CUPS (for printing - currently disabled during GTK4 migration)
    - CppUnit (for running tests)

    INSTALLATION ON LINUX
    =====================

    1) Install build dependencies:

       Ubuntu/Debian:
           sudo apt install meson ninja-build pkg-config \
                            libgtk-4-dev libpoppler-glib-dev \
                            libglib2.0-dev libpango1.0-dev

       Fedora/RHEL:
           sudo dnf install meson ninja-build pkgconfig \
                            gtk4-devel poppler-glib-devel \
                            glib2-devel pango-devel

       Arch Linux:
           sudo pacman -S meson ninja pkgconf gtk4 poppler-glib pango

    2) Get the source code:

       From Git:
           git clone https://github.com/JotaRandom/epdfview.git
           cd epdfview

       From tarball:
           tar xvzf epdfview-<version>.tar.gz
           cd epdfview-<version>

    3) Configure the build:

       Standard configuration (CUPS disabled):
           meson setup builddir -Dcups=disabled

       Custom prefix:
           meson setup builddir --prefix=/usr -Dcups=disabled

       Other options:
           meson setup builddir -Dcups=disabled -Dtests=false

    4) Build the application:

           meson compile -C builddir

       Or using Ninja directly:
           cd builddir
           ninja

    5) (Optional) Run tests:

           meson test -C builddir

    6) Install the application:

           sudo meson install -C builddir

       Or using Ninja:
           cd builddir
           sudo ninja install

    7) Run the application:

           epdfview [file.pdf]

       Or without installing:
           ./builddir/epdfview [file.pdf]

    MESON BUILD OPTIONS
    ===================

    View all options:
        meson configure builddir

    Common options:
        -Dprefix=/usr/local          Install prefix
        -Dcups=enabled|disabled       Enable/disable CUPS printing
        -Dtests=true|false           Build tests
        -Dbuildtype=debug|release    Build type

    Reconfigure existing build:
        meson --reconfigure builddir -Dcups=disabled

    Clean build:
        rm -rf builddir
        meson setup builddir

    TROUBLESHOOTING
    ===============

    Build fails with "GTK4 not found":
        - Ensure GTK4 development packages are installed
        - Check: pkg-config --modversion gtk4

    Build fails with "Poppler not found":
        - Ensure Poppler GLib bindings are installed
        - Check: pkg-config --modversion poppler-glib

    Icons missing when running:
        - Install icon theme: sudo apt install adwaita-icon-theme

    Application won't start:
        - Run with debug output: G_MESSAGES_DEBUG=all ./epdfview
        - Check GTK4 version: pkg-config --modversion gtk4

    MIGRATION FROM GTK3/GTK2
    ========================

    This GTK4 version is a major update from previous GTK2/GTK3 versions.
    Main changes:

    - Build system changed from Autotools to Meson/Ninja
    - Printing temporarily disabled (under GTK4 migration)
    - Traditional menu bar replaced with toolbar and shortcuts
    - Event handling uses modern GTK4 controllers
    - Some window management features removed (GTK4/Wayland)

    See README.md and GTK4_MIGRATION_SUMMARY.md for more details.

    FOR DEVELOPERS
    ==============

    Development build with debug symbols:
        meson setup builddir --buildtype=debug -Dcups=disabled
        meson compile -C builddir

    Run from build directory:
        ./builddir/epdfview

    View build log:
        meson compile -C builddir -v

    UNINSTALLATION
    ==============

    If installed via Meson:
        sudo ninja uninstall -C builddir

    Note: Meson records installation in builddir/meson-logs/install-log.txt
